CHANGES0021: Create AxiomsWork.agda and OpenClosedWork.agda

Summary:
  Created two new "presentation layer" files that organize the content
  from Parts 01-02 into clean, readable, well-documented modules
  following the structure of main-monolithic.tex.

New files:
  work/AxiomsWork.agda (211 lines)
    - Presents the four axioms: Stone Duality, SurjectionsAreFormalSurjections,
      Local Choice, Dependent Choice
    - Documents consequences: Markov's Principle, LLPO, ¬WLPO
    - Lists all postulates and their status
    - Pattern: imports Part02 public + extensive documentation comments

  work/OpenClosedWork.agda (349 lines)
    - Presents the full theory of open and closed propositions
    - Organized into 15 sections matching the tex structure:
      definitions, examples, negation, stability, finite/countable
      operations, De Morgan laws, implication, decidability,
      dependent sums, synthetic topology, surjections from 2^ℕ
    - Pattern: imports Part02 public + extensive documentation comments

Both files follow the same pattern as work/LLPOWork.agda: they import
from existing Part files with `public` re-export and add structured
documentation comments. No existing files were modified.

No decrease in code: these are purely additive new files.
